Synopsis:
   debug [alias|hook  <name>]

Description:
   This command will turn on debugging for a named hook or alias. It
   provides a method to make sure your script provide debugging information
   in a special debug window. In order for the debug window to be created
   you must /set debug first.

   This command with no arguments provides a list of active file descriptors
   that have waiting input/output.

Usage:
   Turn Debugging on:
      /set debug all
      /debug alias public_feer
      /debug hook flood

See Also:
   set(4) debug

